</p>

<p>
  Phishing awareness training is often labelled as security awareness training, but because security posture is basically a free-for-all in the corporate world due to (most likely purposefully) unclear regulations, it gets thrown into the mix as an effective, hollistic solution for a company's security issues. It's a deceitful practice that undermines security awareness training to both the company, and the individual employees who have to use it.
